findings.liver: Hepatic parenchyma appears within normal limits. The contour is smooth. No focal liver mass. The main portal vein is patent with hepatopetal flow. No ascites.
findings.bile_ducts: No intrahepatic biliary dilation. CBD measures 5 mm. No definite evidence of choledocholithiasis.
findings.gallbladder: Distended with multiple layering gallstones noted. Several gallstones reside in the gallbladder neck. No definite gallbladder wall thickening or pericholecystic fluid.
findings.pancreas: Imaged portion appears within normal limits, without masses or pancreatic ductal dilation.
findings.kidneys: Right kidney measures 8.8 cm. Left kidney measures 10.0 cm. Normal cortical echogenicity and corticomedullary differentiation. No evidence of masses, stones, or hydronephrosis.
findings.retroperitoneum: Visualized portions of aorta and IVC are within normal limits.
